773
01:01:57.300 --> 01:01:58.250
Daz: Sure, why not?

774
01:01:58.250 --> 01:02:04.660
Kostadis Roussos: Oh, you do? That's, that's, that's… I will… but… but I, I don't peddle and gossip?

775
01:02:04.850 --> 01:02:07.060
Gabe: I mustn't, but for the investigation.

776
01:02:07.060 --> 01:02:10.120
Kostadis Roussos: Oh, well, yes, of course, for the investigation!

777
01:02:10.270 --> 01:02:15.260
Kostadis Roussos: She then pours you some tea. She's very excited.

778
01:02:18.310 --> 01:02:28.239
Kostadis Roussos: I was bringing the keeper his morning tea when I passed Callan's strong branch on the steps. He had a face like thunder, nearly knocked the tray out of my hands.

779
01:02:29.660 --> 01:02:43.749
Kostadis Roussos: Then she goes, And it must have been around the ninth bell, when Teles of Oste came to visit the Keeper. Those two have never got on well, and the meeting soon descended into a shouting mash. Of course it was hard to make out what they were saying, especially as I wasn't listening.

780
01:02:44.280 --> 01:02:50.389
Kostadis Roussos: Pauses. But I did hear Telus shout, HYPOCRITE at poor Janusi before he stormed out.

781
01:02:51.380 --> 01:02:52.260
Daz: Hmm.

782
01:02:52.580 --> 01:02:58.580
Kostadis Roussos: Right. And then she pauses. Oh, and then there was that Cad Daral Yashenti.

783
01:02:59.400 --> 01:03:09.469
Kostadis Roussos: He's the guy who, gave the book. Was here around the 11th bell, nursing a hangover by the looks of him. Oh, and that's nothing new, he drinks way too much.

784
01:03:09.610 --> 01:03:13.949
Kostadis Roussos: I happen to be doing some dusting up near the keeper's door and chanced to… well…

785
01:03:14.420 --> 01:03:31.379
Kostadis Roussos: accidentally overhear some very unscholarly language being exchanged, You're not fit to be the candle keeps keeper, Daryl shouted at poor Janu, singing, and then something about nothing but a glorified book peddler, whatever that means.

786
01:03:31.960 --> 01:03:32.680
Daz: Mmm.

787
01:03:32.900 --> 01:03:34.859
Kostadis Roussos: And then, finally, she ends.

788
01:03:35.030 --> 01:03:52.189
Kostadis Roussos: But then those Schenbrannigans were nothing but petered bickering compared to what was to come. That devil woman! She gives me the heebie-jeebies! I mean, you take a note, she's literally a devil woman, she's a woman who studies demons and devils.

789
01:03:52.190 --> 01:03:52.810
Gabe: O.

790
01:03:52.810 --> 01:04:00.319
Kostadis Roussos: Right? I mean, it's not… it's not an epithet or an adjective, it's a job function description.

791
01:04:00.620 --> 01:04:01.429
Gabe: Good clarification.

792
01:04:01.430 --> 01:04:04.629
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, yeah, just, just, just wanna make sure that…

793
01:04:04.810 --> 01:04:21.079
Kostadis Roussos: I was never sure but what the keeper saw in her, but he certainly incurred her wrath that morning. Raging she was, screamed that he was a traitor! At what point it sounded like the two of them were acting violently, and then suddenly she stormed out, nearly took the door off its hinges when she left.

794
01:04:21.970 --> 01:04:24.560
Kostadis Roussos: So this happened during the day before midnight.

795
01:04:25.870 --> 01:04:26.670
Kostadis Roussos: Right?

796
01:04:31.940 --> 01:04:33.540
Gabe: Anything after the Devil Woman?

797
01:04:33.540 --> 01:04:35.340
Kostadis Roussos: Well, she then goes…

798
01:04:35.780 --> 01:04:39.040
Kostadis Roussos: Well, it, you know, and by the way, that was what happened during the day.

799
01:04:40.480 --> 01:04:41.749
Daz: What happened tonight?

800
01:04:41.750 --> 01:04:47.650
Kostadis Roussos: Well, she goes, well, then, oh my goodness, you'd think it was… it was… it was the center of Waterdeep.

801
01:04:49.880 --> 01:04:51.830
Kostadis Roussos: Everybody had… you have…

802
01:04:52.010 --> 01:04:59.929
Kostadis Roussos: She goes, Feminoor came to visit Genusi at 9pm. She didn't stay long, leaving some 15 to 20 minutes… later.

803
01:05:03.240 --> 01:05:19.879
Kostadis Roussos: Then he came back at 10.30pm, drunk as a skunk, he pounded on Janusi's door until the keeper admitted him, and then they had another loud argument. Shortly after that, I heard him slam the door and saw the great reader rushing back down the stairs. I'd never seen him run away so fast.

804
01:05:21.020 --> 01:05:23.950
Ben Pfaff: Well, this definitely sounds like somebody we need to talk to.

805
01:05:24.800 --> 01:05:27.420
Joe Beda: Who was, who was this at this last one? Was…

806
01:05:27.420 --> 01:05:30.839
Kostadis Roussos: Daral, that's the guy who… Okay. The CAD.

807
01:05:31.220 --> 01:05:32.030
Kostadis Roussos: Right?

808
01:05:32.410 --> 01:05:40.069
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah. And then she goes, and then… and I was about to go to sleep, and then she says, would you like some tea? She points to Thorne.

809
01:05:40.950 --> 01:05:42.389
Joe Beda: No thank you, I'm good.

810
01:05:42.720 --> 01:05:44.970
Kostadis Roussos: Oh. Solitaire?

811
01:05:44.970 --> 01:05:47.140
Gabe: Yes, I love… Absolutely!

812
01:05:47.140 --> 01:05:52.950
Kostadis Roussos: So he's… she's very excited, and she goes, She sits down with me.

813
01:05:53.230 --> 01:06:02.860
Kostadis Roussos: I was… I just had gotten ready to go to sleep, I had going to have my beauty sleep, when I was awoken by the midnight chimes of the bell tower.

