Kostadis Roussos: Right.

871
01:09:56.240 --> 01:10:01.529
Kostadis Roussos: There was a prophecy that on the longest night, the keeper falls.

872
01:10:03.190 --> 01:10:04.360
Kostadis Roussos: At midnight.

873
01:10:07.540 --> 01:10:09.790
Kostadis Roussos: And so Janusi is very much a keeper.

874
01:10:10.050 --> 01:10:14.080
Ben Pfaff: Was there anything to suggest that this was the longest night of some kind?

875
01:10:14.080 --> 01:10:17.740
Kostadis Roussos: Yes, because it's, deep winter, so it's the longest night of the year.

876
01:10:18.040 --> 01:10:19.429
Joe Beda: So it's like winter solstice type thing?

877
01:10:19.430 --> 01:10:21.189
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, yep, winter solstice, I think.

878
01:10:21.840 --> 01:10:27.579
Gabe: Does, does a nice… Keeper know why they rung the midnight bell?

879
01:10:28.640 --> 01:10:31.280
Kostadis Roussos: The midnight bell?

880
01:10:31.430 --> 01:10:34.269
Gabe: Yeah, didn't you say that was unusual? She woke up because of the…

881
01:10:34.270 --> 01:10:37.280
Kostadis Roussos: No, no, no, she woke up because she heard an unusual thud.

882
01:10:37.810 --> 01:10:40.119
Gabe: Oh, that woke her up.

883
01:10:40.620 --> 01:10:46.019
Ben Pfaff: I asked her if the thud could be the statue falling over.

884
01:10:47.580 --> 01:10:54.160
Kostadis Roussos: Oh, no, no, no, that, that, it, no, no, I… I… She pauses. I think…

885
01:10:54.680 --> 01:11:01.669
Kostadis Roussos: She looks at Thorin awfully, and says, I think it was Janusi dying.

886
01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:04.560
Ben Pfaff: You think it was him falling?

887
01:11:04.560 --> 01:11:05.040
Kostadis Roussos: Yes.

888
01:11:05.040 --> 01:11:05.660
Daz: Hmm.

889
01:11:07.450 --> 01:11:09.869
Ben Pfaff: Did you hear anything that could be the statue?

890
01:11:10.560 --> 01:11:14.329
Kostadis Roussos: No, the statue happened earlier.

891
